The White House respects the decision of Japanese Prime Minister Hatoyama to step down and believes that the selection of the next Prime Minister is a matter for the Japanese people and political process. The US-Japan bilateral relationship is strong and rooted in common interests and values. The alliance has thrived under each Japanese Prime Minister and US President in the past 50 years and will continue to strengthen in the future. The US will continue to work closely with the Japanese government and the next Prime Minister on various issues.